caption: Love this place! The food is soulful and so is the owner + staff. Highly recommend (if they’re still open). Does anyone know if they made it through COVID?

The food was pretty good, my non-vegan friend really enjoyed the food. The friendliness, vibe, coziness of the space was what truly made it a 5/5! The owner is absolutely lovely, and so are the rest of the staff.  Really tiny but feels like you’re with family.
Too good. Get up early to order the cake :)
Delicious nachos and hibiscus tea! You must try this place!
Excellent food but please put your menu in Spanish it is also better for those who have difficulty reading English thanks

The good here is delicious and so very flavorful! Me and my friends got 3 dishes and shared and my favorite was the crab cake. I'm not vegan myself so I don't have too much meat-alternative experience to compare it to but I can say everything was delicious!!
Not only was the food delicious the customer service was off the hook. This is where i want to spend my money. On businessthat care about their customers.
Service great. Food decent
Get the Greedi Veggie Bowl, highly recommend!

**UPDATE** 8/05/18 Latisha (the owner) responded to my feedback and offered to personally deliver me food or have me come back in for a meal on her to make up for my original experience.  I decided to take her up on the offer to come back to the restaurant. My friend and I came in today around 1:00pm for the weekend brunch. They were packed and very busy and running low/out of certain items but Latisha made sure she took care of us. We wanted 2 orders of French Toast but they only had enough left for one, so we ordered French toast, Pancakes Berries N Coco Cream and a Soy Sausage Tofu Scramble & Cheese Platter. Initially we ordered it to go since there was no space and they were so slammed, but eventually while we were waiting, seats at the bar opened up and we decided to dine in since half of our food had been ready and packaged for awhile, but the pancakes were taking longer to be made.  The French Toast was DELICIOUS. The syrup had almost a burbon flavor to it, along with the strawberries & blueberries and the coco cream was amazing. The bread itself was a little thin but tasted great! The pancakes were also tasty, but they were basically the same as the french toast (same toppings). The Sausage Tofu Scramble was ok... not the greatest, but I did enjoy the sausage. We were also missing the avocado toast with it, but they were so slammed and we had been there for awhile, so I didn't want to wait for it.  Latisha was bright and cheery and made conversation with us throughout or time in the space. She was clearly working very hard to keep things running smoothly and make sure all the orders were on point. I truly appreciated her commitment to making sure my friend and I felt welcomed and appreciated as a customers.  I feel like if there was maybe at least one more staff member working at Latisha's commitment level to the food and customer experience that this place would be absolutely INCREDIBLE. I know they're still a brand new establishment and working out some kinks, but I hope it continues to grow and elevate with dedicated employees.  But I am super thankful for Latisha's personal commitment to her customers. Thank you for making things right for us!
Everything was so good! We had the cauliflower po boy, jerk chicken wrap, crab cake sliders, lemonade... all vegan of course!!!
Food was served quickly, team very friendly, and food tasted awesome
Delicious but too expensive. I need more sauce on the Po boys.

I am so glad I found this place!!! Even though they are a bit pricey, the food is amazing! They have amazing customer service! Their fries are all hand cut and you can even see them doing it from the pickup window. Their Mac and goodness is oh my goodness! It is soooo good that it’s hard to believe there is no actual dairy in there! My only complaint about it would be the price. I paid $7 for a small side order and don’t believe that I got enough for what I paid for. Their kale is super delicious with a mildly sweet undertone that keeps you coming for more! Their Jerk chicken wasn’t all that jerk-y and definitely could have used more of the Caribbean spices.
Absolutely delicious and decadent and exactly what I wanted. GF options and vegan! I’m in heaven. I got the fried oyster mushroom tacos and Mac and goodness. Will be ordering again! Thank you!
The worst food I ever taste the service was bad !! And the was calling people racial words
Ordered cauliflower bites with sweet chilli and received oily cauliflower fried in dough with ketchup. Very unsatisfactory for $12
This place is a blessing. So happy it exists. The chef is such a boss!! OMG BEST TOFU SCRAMBLE IVE HAD IN MY LIFE.
Delicious
Food is great. The crispy cauliflower is one of my favorites. Chickpea omelette is flavorful and fulfilling.. The cheesey grits is official
This was a great find on my vegan eatery will definitely be returning
Awesome food!! Wow - who knew plants could taste so good. Dope spot. Definitely my go to now!! Great customer service as well.
The food was amazing! Staff was incredible! Service was on the slow side, (found out from a member from our group that there was a malfunction). Great atmosphere 💖
Amazing and delicious vegan food. The fish and grits is my fav brunch item. From a non vegan who has never enjoyed vegan food before.

I called at 7pm and no one answered the phone, drove 15 minutes to get there. As soon as I walk in two women behind the counter gave me a dirty look and asked if I was picking up...to which i answered no...so they both ignored me and kept cleaning. I stood there with my partner waiting for some type of customer service....t ok which we got none! Everything was packed up and all the stools were on top of the table. So we left.  I understand it's almost closing time but its still 30 minutes till....at least offer us what ever you have  available or say hey we are almost closing but I can offer you the following....something jeez...horrible service...first and last time. Went in over a year ago and the owner was so hospitable and warm. Now I dont live as close so I've  ordered through UberEats. Fast forward to a few days ago I see a first! A vegan restaurant with an alkaline vegan option and it was delicious! Black woman owned,  in Brooklyn, great service, great food!
The best Vegan Restaurant in the New York City.
Everything is delicious, but make absolutely sure that you leave room for dessert, as the cakes are great: especially the carrot cake and the apple spice cheesecake!

Absolutely amazing!!! Loved the soul bowl. Although I am not a fan of soy I got the fried chicken option. It was delicious.. I wish I ordered in advance the wait is about 15 min. Definitely worth the wait.
The cauliflower bites and the soul bowl with Mac n cheese is probably my favorite meal in the neighborhood. They are also happy to fill your own Tupperware. Friendly people who listen to good music.

Great take out spot. Plenty of options. The food was very flavorful. The quaint space has a warm and welcoming ambiance. The music selection set the vibe. The friendly staff was accommodating to our rushed schedule. The service was timely as they served many patrons within a half hour, effortlessly. We had the burger and fish sandwich, both with fresh made fries. We also had the lemon cake and sweet potato cheesecake. The hibiscus tea was refreshing. We definitely recommend checking out this spot, both local and those traveling through.
The food was excellent as usual but the staff's energy is off a bit. We need that Latisha energy back in there !!
Good food
I did not buy anything. Looking forward to visiting again to try the food.
Ladies are awesome food delicious
Food(Greedi Soul bowl) is very clean well seasoned as I am Caribbean delicious as well as the carrot cake. It was my first time and I will make it a usual
Food is beyond delicious

First veegan restaurant and loved it! It's a tiny place with maybe 8 sittings in the whole place but the food was prepared with love. The two ladies that run the place have a passion and you can taste it!

They were out of mac & cheese. What I got was overcooked kale & soy chicken - that tasted like frozen ones you get at the supermart. In fact, I think I saw it at T.Joes today! Heavy on carbs, bland flavor, not enjoyable. What's worse is their price - $15? & overpriced sweetened drinks that wasn't good. I didn't go to a vegan place to get supermart food at thrice the price.
Food was amazing! I was satisfied and their BANANA PUDDING CHEESECAKE is to die for. I wish them luck in their business.
Foods good, but such slow service and a bit over priced certain items.  $8 for 9 pieces of plantain, that is crazy as hell

Really good food! I had the soul bowl and it was delicous. The service was very fast.
Excellent service and food!! This took vegan food to the next level, the flavor and overall taste knocked my socks off. I will definitely be coming back again and bringing a friend.  😋

Okay, so can we talk about this place!?!?! I absolutely loovvee Greedi Vegan!  Unfortunately I only took a photo of one thing that I bought; but I have tried a plethora of their menu and it NEVER disappoints! The staff is very helpful (especially if it's your first time) with navigating the menu and choosing the food items that call to your soul. They also have a very warming environment there where even the customers welcomes each customer with open arms. Their desserts are finger licking good, and the serving sizes are definitely more than enough (for anyone that is curious)...and the pricing is perfect. I would definitely recommend their soul bowl🥰 and their nacho fries (as pictured). A must go-to whenever I am in the neighborhood!
This food is soooooooo GOOD!
It a good Vegan restaurant but it small. It only take out
Quick service,delicious options,knowledgeable staff,Mellow atmosphere.Wished it was spacious.
Had the Mac and cheese, fish sandwich and pb&j cheesecake for desert. Everything was sooo good!!! Service was great too🤗

How can such a teensy spot whip up vegan food with flavor this big!? We visited from Cincinnati, our first stop in Brooklyn. I was set back by how small it was but three of us sat comfortably at the counter.  Honest guidance from the staff directed us to some great choices. If you like traditional soul food, the Soul Bowl won’t disappoint packed with old and new flavors. And how can you fry up oyster mushrooms and make the best Po’ boy north of Wachahatchie? Must I go to a vegan spot to have great chips (aka steak fries)? Yes. Friendly and welcoming yes...willing to spill the beans on what was in the kale...nope!
Very nice small intimate place to get a good food. Not to mention the menu items are interesting especially the mac and cheese and  nachos which I highly recommend
I am happy that I found this great kitchen/ restaurant. The food was outstanding and the cook was extraordinary. I'll go back there for sure.

Ordered Greedi Ginger fried plantain and jerk bowl yesterday afternoon coming from work through Uber eats.  I'm not sure if it's the preparation but those plantains were not fully fried, there were sides of bright yellow. The portion amount seem small especially given the large packaging. The sauce was bland and too thick for my liking, almost a consistency of mayonnaise. Not worth the price.  The sweet potatoes were watery, not much flavor. The red cabbage slaw was bland, no flavor and was unnecessary to add. The mac and cheese wasn't cheesy enough for my liking. The jerk chicken flavor couldn't make up for the texture of the vegan meat. overall the entire dish was bland, watery, lacked flavor and was a disappoint. There are much better vegan restaurants out there in Brooklyn that offer much more flavor, firmer texture and better portion size for a lower price. Won't be ordering from here again.
Very friendly staff, great options and very tasty good
Great food, great staff, fun guests.

Excellent food. Great service!

Seriously had the best meal and best time for lunch today at Greedi Vegan! The owner Latisha (hope I spelled that right) was unbelievably kind, funny, wise, supportive (of me and the other girls eating at the bar) and cooked our delicious food all at the same time. I had the nachos with chicken and then the soul bowl which had some of the best Mac and cheese I’ve ever tasted. Amazing food, vibes and conversation. I will be back soon. ❤️ Latisha your vision for your restaurant is exactly the experience I had today...I felt it!!

Fantastic plant place

Everything was so good I had the MAC & Cheese & the spicy bowl, and the meatballs everything was flavorful. That’s what I’m big on is FLAVOR! It tasted like actual food and not bland or grassy.

All I can say its WOW!!!!!!!!!!!! The food was excellent, blew My taste buds away. And the vegan based upside down pineapple cake and carrot cakes!!!! OMG !! The staff was the best, Very, very nice, I wish I remembered their names, I was there Saturday August 3rd. Looking foward to going back and eating something different:)

I could tell that they put care into every interaction and task at hand. The music was great and even though the restaurant is super small, it didn’t feel claustrophobic. I’ll definitely be back!

First time visit. Didn't go to far out ( portabella sliders and fried plantains). Service was good and homemade green tea lemonade was delicious. Will definitely go back. They mentioned there was another location on Ralph Av

The food was absolutely delicious and though the space is small, it is a welcoming one. Likewise, the customer service was wonderful. I had the beyond burger, which they topped with mixed greens and a light spicy sauce. I loved every bite. The fries were so chunky, crispy, and yummy. They were selling a delicious apple, cucumber ginger juice and I had some of that as well. At the end, I was offered a slice of cheesecake, and it was delicious. Here is my complaint, this place is too expensive. The cheesecake alone was $7.50 and thought it was offered, I was not told the price. I'm searching for a vegan spot with delicious food, but not such high prices. If price isn't a factor for you, you will love this spot!
A tiny hole in the wall with some of the most delicious vegan food I’ve had in NYC.

The space is quite small, but the owner and every employee makes it feel very homey which separates it from other hipster vegan places. You feel good when eating, especially since they provide clean and comforting meals. It's definitely worth the money and experience and will become a top fav of mine.
Amazing!! Great food generous portions at a decent price. Place is cosy inside.

great fiid but really expensive

I have been wanting to try this place for a long time, and I have to say I wasn’t disappointed with what I had. I tried a jerk chicken sandwich and a side of plantains. However, I’ve been a vegetarian for 25 years and the biggest issue my family and I always had was access to healthy, tasty and affordable vegetarian/vegan foods!! It’s such a shame that this same type is cuisine can’t be offered at a more accessible price. The wrap I had was pretty tasty, but really how often is a customer going to pay 17 dollars for a wrap to go with no sides, no drink just a wrap? I want to be able to support local businesses like this one and will go when I can, but it’s still a shame that people gotta break the pocket to enjoy a good vegan meal.
Good, but under seasoned and the ingredients were pretty basic for the price point.

Literally came in to order food to go, very pregnant and was told after paying $25 that they have no plastic utensils to go. And maybe I should check across the street. That left a sour taste in my mouth.
I have been a handful of times, and loved it every single time. Looking forward to GV2. Much success and love to the owners. Peace

I honestly don't know where to begin. INCREDIBLE vegan food, absurdly friendly and welcoming atmosphere, and the owner is soooo sweet! My girlfriend and I had such a good time! We are making it one of our favorite go-to Brooklyn restaurants! I hope they continue to grow, as both a restaurant and business.
Vegan soul food that tasted like love

A wonderful experience. Nice vibes, friendly staff, comfortable/ cozy environment along with incredible food. I loved the soul bowl with fried oyster mushrooms.  Amazing!!  I took a slice of strawberry key lime pie home. Was kind of nervous to try it because I find it hard to find good vegan desserts. However, that slice was truly heavenly. Worth every penny!  I look forward to going back real soon and continuing to support Chef Latisha. She is not only very friendly and welcoming, she's super passionate about the dishes she creates. You can taste that in her food.  Continued growth and success to Greedi Vegan!! Thank you for a great culinary experience. ❤

I don't usually leave reviews but this delicious vegan hot spot deserves 10 stars!! Not only is the food incredible but the atmosphere is so welcoming. The owner and staff recognize me and are always so happy to see me even though I've only bee there a handful of times. Their sliders are beyond this world and their carrot cake is the best I've ever had! Love this place and will be going back very soon.
Very nice staff good food
Fresh, creative, and really tasty.
The portions are kid sized and really overpriced for what we ordered. It didn't taste   great either, something we could easily make for a fraction of the price at home.

I've  been there several times and the food is yummy... if you are into vegan food.  My favs are the vegan beef and the mushroom sliders, plantains with that sauce, the yuca fries,the soul bowl was cool and the carrot cake is yummy. The owner is super friendly as well as the rest of the staff there. Deff worth a shot wether you are vegan or  not . One of the best restaurants in Brooklyn. Period. Just try once.
Very small, but omg! So good! I had the soul bowl with sweet potatoes, Mac & cheese, kale, and chicken! Large portions and decent prices. Friendly staff!
great food and kind and wonderful  staff.
Breakfast was great.
I stopped in for the first time and ordered Greedi Yam fries, $8 + tax although tasty, you get more in McDonald's small fry.
Delicious food, great prices, and friendly staff. Ya can't go wrong at greedi vegan!
Everything was delicious and it was just a nice place to be!
The best in Crown heights , hands down!

Hey soul sistah! Nah but for real though. Put this place on your list for vegan restaurants in Brooklyn! They're currently working on spot number 2. So that ought to tell you. Food is banging. Not gonna lie it takes a while because it's freshly made! So order ahead. Don't take my word for it. Go check it out for yourself. The oyster mushroom po'boy and yucca fries I'd fight you for👊🏿. And bonus it's black owned so it's a no brainer! Support support support
Warm and friendly environment! Delicious plant based food😊👅.
Awesome

This spot is off the chain. I'm not a vegan, I met my cousin there and I enjoyed everything I ate. Lots of flavor and season with fresh herbs  and vegetables, make me want to turn vegan. Great spot! I will return very soon.

Trop delicieux 😍 Being vegan only gets better with Greedi Vegan. This place is cozy and the people there are super nice. The owner Laeticia has such a vibrant energy that is so inviting. We had the crispy cauli bites, soul bowl, the sliders and the forest cake. Everything was made fresh. We're definitely coming back. Thank you for providing the neighborhood with amazing vegan food 🙏

As a meat eater, this is the best burger I've ever had. Cauliflower nuggets beat out chicken. Desserts sweet with extra hugs and kisses not sugar.  Gladly donated to their Kickstarter to get them into bed stuy.  Questioning why I eat meat after this meal.  Super cozy, awesome friendly  staff,  and the owner is 100% awesome.  Do yourself a solid. Try everything here

Had the bowl with my girlfriend with some of the apple hibiscus tea and it was simply delicious. Cute and tiny environment and the staff were very pleasant, eager to serve, and were exceptional all they way around.
The food was delicious. The owner is very inviting. Great establishment.
Good little eat.. Nice take outs
Excellent food & exceptional service. What a Great combination!!

Decided to stop at this cute new place to pick up lunch. The owner was so warm and friendly, we felt so welcome here. I would highly recommend the cauliflower bites because they were so crispy and fresh. The red chilli sauce is the best!
Greedi Vegan is amazing! One of my favorite vegan restaurants
The food is amazing.

I had the veggie soul bowl which consisted of greens, mac and cheese, sweet potatoes and veggie chicken. It was an interesting and tasty meal. The flavors all blended well together. The menu had a lot of different vegan entrees. Good eating!!!

The cauliflower bites we're delish! The sweet potato fries were horrible, they didn't taste good and the portion size was a total waste of $8. I'm definitely going back to try other items just won't get the fries.
Awesome place,great vibes!

Food was fantastic. I am not even vegan and enjoyed everything about my meal. I had the soul bowl which consisted of fried "chick'n" set atop of wild rice, spinach and sweet potatoes. The texture of the chick'n was mimic real chicken so well. The food was perfectly seasoned. I did not need to add anything.  My bf got the fish and grits with goat cheese toast. His meal too was delish. Latisha, the owner, is very personable and a hoot to talk with. I have definitely added this to my go to restaurants.  After I ate and the food wasgone, I remembered to take a pic...next time I will remember before I eat as even the presentation was good.
Super yummy food and passionate, friendly workers. Your day improves after a Greedi Vegan visit. Love supporting this business <3
Lasagna was great, cool owner and helper!
Nice menu, friendly staff, and really tasty mac and 'cheese'!
Our experience here was amazing! We immediately felt comfortable, right at home. Latisha is great!!! Not to mention how absolutely delicious food here is.
DELICIOUS HEALTHY SATISFYING FLAVORFUL and FRESH WONDERFUL SERVICE LOVE THIS PLACE I WILL RECOMMEND

There are so many wonderful things to say about this place, I don't know where to begin! First of all the staff is incredible. They are so warm, friendly, and hospitable, they make you feel like you're eating at a relative's house.  The food is indescribable. I had to double check and make sure the food was vegan because the meatball sliders were out of this world. The veggie tacos were well seasoned and had a creamy, slightly sweet sauce that tied everything together. The mushroom sliders were not only delicious but hearty and filling as well. My mostly meat eating brother-in-law was so impressed with his spicy bowl he commented that he would try being vegan if he could "eat this well every day." We also ordered all the fries (yucca, yam, and plantain) and loved the chipotle avocado sauce that came with them. The meal ended with a moist chocolate cake with a frosting that was light, fluffy, and perfectly sweet (in other words not too sweet).  The only downside was that I couldn't order more because I was stuffed. We will definitely be going there again.  I am so glad we found this place!
yummy french toast and tofu scramble! thank you!

Wasn’t what I was hoping for... Prepackaged soy meat and vegan cheese, all on top of packaged (slighty stale) nachos.  Nothing was fresh. Not even the salsa and guacamole. Those came from a store bought container too.  Hopefully next time (gonna try brunch some time) I’ll have a better experience.
I love the gluten free mac and cheese

Food takes a long time to be prepared even when no one else is around. I had the fish tacos and the tortilla shells came from a box which were stale. The salsa was bad, had a sour taste which makes me question how fresh and sanitary this place is. Menu says avocado, but it is guacamole from a packaged container. Many items are not fresh or cared for properly. I will not recommend this restaurant to anyone.
Delicious food and super friendly staff. Can’t wait to go back soon!! And my non-vegan boyfriend also loved it!

Walked by the restaurant and saw a "GRADE PENDING" showing and was curious to know why.  I looked online with the NY Dept of Health and saw it had 34 violation points!  28 points gets a letter C - EEEK!!! The sanitary violations that were listed included "evidence of mice or live mice present" "filth flies or food/refuse/sewage-associated flies present" "pesticide use not in accordance with label or applicable laws".  These were just a few - there were more.  Hopefully the owner is fixing these issues. Until then, I pass on eating there!!
Excellent food, service and great owner and staff!
Nice, quaint, eatery. Well run and organized. Food is simply delish and well thought out and put together. I will definitely be a regular customer. Kudos to you‼️Keep up the great work‼️
I LOVE the food YAY!!! Will be back thank you Blessings
Great food, vibes & service.
Great food, Great staff!
Great place,  excellent food, many delicious options.  Will definitely come again and again

just came from here, and got the fish n festival. Smallest food portion I've ever seen with 2 minisule pieces and came with a soggy side salad and was charged 15$ for the meal. gentrification at its worst.
a wholesome experience - food, energy, and exchange were all pure and rooted in love🌻

AMAZING food! The soul bowl had the best vegan crab cakes I've ever tried! Excellent meals for reasonable prices and quick, friendly service! Adam and Diangelo were a delight! I work at a vegan restaurant as well and am super impressed by this place! Glad I finally stopped in!
Loved it and will be back. Small, cute shop with incredible vegan options and great service.

So good! I went during brunch and had the tofu scramble and a side of cheese grits. The avocado toast and curried potatoes were amazing! This was the first place I've found with vegan cheese grits. they were awesome too. The staff was warm and friendly I plan to keep coming here!
The food wasnt good or enticing at all the service was great and very pleasant convo with the staff...but me and my lady agreed the food wasnt good. Especially for those prices
Great guess experience and mini burgers
Love this little spot! I shared the soul bowl and the cauli bites. So good! The textures and flavors were on point. I will definitely return

Food was great. Service was great, but receiving your food in a timely manner is the worst. Menu options are great but I think it’s too advanced for the size of the restaurant (very small) and the cooks preparing the food. Accuracy is a must. The cook must learn how to prepare the same quality of food with speed. Not sure if they are not provided with the proper equipment (electric stove 👎🏾), the containers used to hold food are too small, so they’re constantly cooking, which slows everything down, absolutely no counter space for them to prep properly. So my 2 stars is for the extremely long wait time and the limited of space for the cooks.
If you love yourself and your body please try the food. You can taste the love!

A wonderful owner, well mannered and kind with her words. A great menu selection, and did not feel oily and greasy like so much processed vegan food available now a days. We felt we enjoyed the company of her and the two gentlemen throughout our meal, great conversation! A pleasure to support local businesses promoting a vegan lifestyle. We will be returning customers!
The staff were really friendly.  Menu options sounded really interesting but my meal was quite bland.  Not much space if you plan to dine in.

Really good food for the price, good size portions. Had the sliders and the nachos, excellent! Just wish the nachos had more cheese on them, the bottom 50% of the chips were dry but the ingredients were on point, hella delicious. Love the people and the atmosphere. Will be back.

Food is amazing. Please dont allow negative comments stop you from visiting this healthy black owned business. They are fairly new so the service is a little slow but if you call ahead of going you can get your food on time McDonald's and Wendy's service suck but people still go. The staff and the owner is very friendly and and will do anything for you to have a great experience sometimes you go and the food is sold out and she would try her best to come up with something just to make you happy

Came to Greedi Vegan because my boyfriend and I were craving brunch food. The place is a bit tight but the food was so good! I ordered French toast and my boyfriend ordered the pancakes. The only critique I have is that they were out of the cheese grits. So if you really want something on the menu COME EARLY. Our food was so good that we stayed for lunch and ordered Mac & cheese. Great spot if you love flavored vegan food.
Soulful people, delicious food. So happy my vegan visitor suggested we go here
Portobello mushroom sliders for the win. Friendly service and fresh ingredients. Great for a quick bite!

Stumbled upon this gem on a girls trip to Brooklyn! The staff was lovely, and the food was on point. We ordered the tofu scramble & avocado toast, the sausage tofu scramble sandwich, and the grits and vegan beef gravy. Everything was so flavorful, we couldn’t stop picking off one another’s plates! Open kitchen, home-style cooking, outdoor seating, friendly conversation...definitely will return!
